data.title: FRANKLINTON NEW ERA/LEADER OBITUARY INDEX
data.text:
In 1896 the Franklinton New Era’s editor was Francis W. Mather. The location was located at the Old School Building. This paper was published every Thursday. During the years, the newspaper’s name has been changed from the Franklinton New Era to New Era to The Era Leader. This newspaper is now being published on Wednesday.

The earliest newspaper on microfilm is in 1896. The early years of newspapers are very scattered. Missing years: 1949
